wer & Around Todoroki Valley Ebisu Haneda & Around Jiyugaoka Oshima Island Toshima Island Niijima Island Shikinejima Island Kozushima Island Miyakejima Island Mikurajima Island Hachijojima Island Aogashima Island Chichijima Island Hahajima Island Mitaka, Musashino & Around Chofu, Fuchu & Around Kunitachi, Tachikawa & Around Tama Machida Nishi Tokyo Hachioji Mt. Takao & Around Okutama & Around\n    * #guide services\n    * #Shibuya\n    * #Aoyama & Omotesando\n    * #Akihabara\n    * #Light-up (Illumination)\n    * #Art & Museums\nSearch results: 0\n[Search](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/js/en_search.xml)\n  * [Listen](https://app-as.readspeaker.com/cgi-bin/rsent?customerid=8783&lang=en_us&readclass=banner_top_cnt,banner_result_cnt,visual_detail,top_pankuzu&readid=tmp_main&url=)\n  * [Share this page](javascript:void\\(0\\);)\nShare this page\n    * [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.gotokyo.org/en/story/guide/sightseeing-spots-for-the-family/index.html)\n    * [X (Twitter)](https://twitter.com/share?url=https://www.gotokyo.org/en/story/guide/sightseeing-spots-for-the-family/index.html&text=Sightseeing%20Spots%20for%20the%20Family&hashtags=gotokyo)\n    * Email\n    * [Copy URL](javascript:void\\(0\\);)\n  * [FAVORITES](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/favorites/index.html)\n  * [Menu](javascript:void\\(0\\);)\nSelect Language 日本語 ENGLISH 中文(简体) 中文(繁體/正體) 한글 ภาษาไทย DEUTSCH ITALIANO ESPAÑOL FRANÇAIS\n\n\n[ ![Ticket Click](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_ticket_btn.webp) ![Ticket Click](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_ticket_btn_hover.webp) ](https://www.tickets.gotokyo.org/en/?utm_source=gotokyo&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=tickets_redirect&utm_content=menu)\n[ ![Useful info](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_useful_btn.webp) ![Useful info](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_useful_btn_hover.webp) ](javascript:void\\(0\\))\n  * [ ![For your safety](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_safety_btn.webp) ![For your safety](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_safety_btn_hv.webp) ](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/plan/health-safety/index.html)\n  * [ ![Manners & Customs](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_manners_btn.webp) ![Manners & Customs](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_manners_btn_hv.webp) ](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/plan/customs-culture/index.html)\n  * [ ![Ask AI](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_ask_btn.png) ![Ask AI](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/icon/fixed_ask_btn_hv.png) ](https://app.tokyo-onlineguide-ai.org/chat?utm_source=askai&utm_medium=cpc&utm_campaign=campaign_1&lang=en)\n\n\nMain content starts here.\n  * [Visit Tokyo](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/index.html) | \n  * [EXPERIENCES](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/experiences/index.html) | \n  * [Best things to do in Tokyo tailored to your preferences](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/see-and-do/index.html) | \n  * [Top tourist attractions in Tokyo: the best sightseeing spots](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/see-and-do/attractions/index.html) | \n  * Sightseeing Spots for the Family\n\n\n![](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/story/guide/sightseeing-spots-for-the-family/images/main.webp)\nUpdated: January 28, 2026\n# Sightseeing Spots for the Family\n## Discover Tokyo's fun, surprisingly family-friendly side\nTokyo can be both ultra-stimulating and mind-bogglingly bewildering. If you are traveling with a family, it is important to plan ahead. While Tokyo can be overwhelming, don't forget to focus on the fun. The city is safe, multilingual signage is increasingly plentiful and transport is famously efficient.\n### Tips\n  * If your children are under six, public transportation is free; for older children, tickets are usually reduced\n  * Avoid travel during peak hour, when public transport and road traffic become famously congested\n  * Prioritize indoor activities during summer when temperatures soar and the weather is steamy and humid\n  * From basement to rooftop, Tokyo's department stores are your friend. Visit the former for food tastings at depachika food halls, stop in-between for diaper changes and toilet stops, and head to the roofs where you'll often find playgrounds or gardens to run around\n\n\n### Tokyo characters\nVisit Japan and you'll come face to face with a playbook of kid-friendly characters and mascots. Some are local, such as Hello Kitty or Studio Ghibli's Totoro at the Ghibli Museum, Mitaka, or some, like Snoopy, hail from further afield. From retail outlets to cafes, and from museums to theme parks, how you engage with these characters is up to you.\n![](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo/images/story/guide/sightseeing-spots-for-the-family/sub_001.webp)\n### Parks and gardens\nTokyo's parks and outdoor spaces provide a welcome respite from the urban landscape and relentless pace of the city. You can easily spend a day at places like Ueno Park in eastern Tokyo, which comprises playgrounds, shrines, a lake and the Ueno Zoo. Elegant and traditional gardens like the Hama-rikyu Gardens and Arisugawa Park have ample space for children to explore and wander, while riverside Futakotamagawa, only 15 minutes by train from Shibuya, combines parklands, family-friendly eateries and river banks.\n![](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo/images/story/guide/sightseeing-spots-for-the-family/sub_002.webp)\n### Only in Tokyo\nFor once-in-a-lifetime and only-in-Tokyo experiences, consider visiting Shinjuku's Ninja Trick House for an intimate chance to learn about these masters of secrecy and espionage. Hands-on but less Japanese is KidZania Tokyo, an indoor theme park where children aged 3-15 are invited to role play adult jobs. Plan your visit for Wednesdays, when English is pretty much the lingua de franca.\n![](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo/images/story/guide/sightseeing-spots-for-the-family/sub_003.webp)\n### World-class views\nTokyo's sheer size and density can be overwhelming. Gain perspective and be “on top of the world” by heading up high. Visit soaring Tokyo Skytree for unsurpassed views of Tokyo and surrounding areas, the free observation decks at the Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building in Shinjuku to glimpse Mt. Fuji and for something completely different, the rooftop Sunshine Aquarium in Ikebukuro, to see sea animals frolicking against the sky.\n![](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo/images/story/guide/sightseeing-spots-for-the-family/sub_004.webp)\n## for the Family\n## Find Out More\n[GO TOKYO](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/index.html)\n  * [![facebook](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/footer/facebook_icon.png)](https://www.facebook.com/GoTokyo.en/)\n  * [![X \\(Twitter\\)](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/footer/twitter_icon.png)](https://twitter.com/GOTOKYOofficial)\n  * [![You Tube](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/footer/youtube_icon.png)](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC-C1xHOmZO8R-l572ABZ0IQ)\n  * [![instagram](https://www.gotokyo.org/shared/site_gotokyo_rn/images/footer/insta_icon.png)](https://www.instagram.com/tokyotokyooldmeetsnew/)\n\n\n  * [About This Site](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/about-tcvb/index.html)\n  * [Cookie](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/cookie-policy/index.html)\n  * [Sitemap](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/sitemap/index.html)\n  * [Links](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/links/index.html)\n  * [Contact](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/contact/index.html)\n  * [Font Size and Color](https://www.gotokyo.org/en/font-and-color/index.html)\n  * [About Us](https://www.tcvb.or.jp/en/)\n\n\n[Tripadvisor](https://www.tripadvisor.com/Tourism-g1023181-Tokyo_Prefecture_Kanto-Vacations.html?m=17153)\nCopyright © Tokyo Convention & Visitors Bureau. All rights r